al">Re: LOH - now an uber taunt</font></B><HR><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Ummm guys... learn to use this to your advantage.<br>
<br>
First off... if you take the DT off of any mob, you've possibly stunned it a couple times, and you're taking the place of a warrior or rogue or caster that can do more damage/healing than you can.  You're a paladin... willing to sacrifice your life for the good of the group... act like it.<br>
<br>
One of the best strategies that paladins can use to contribute to a high HP boss/demi/dragon/god raid... use LOH on the main tank very early in the fight... use DA and continue taunting... every bit of damage that get absorbed while you're using DA is mana that you have saved the clerics and time you have bought the rogues/warriors/rangers.<br>
<br>
Yes, LOH is an uber taunt... but then again... that's your job isn't it?<br>
<br>
Otter Antilles<br>
